! Authoring a contribution

Cascade-palette is engineered to be extended by ''one tiddler per cascade edge''. The vast majority of integrations never touch JavaScript. Pick the right tag, set the right `ca-*` fields, save — restart only if you also added a JS module (filter operator, widget, startup).

|!You want to add… |!Tag the tiddler with… |!Required fields |!See worked examples in |
|A new menu entry (root stage) |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry` |`ca-name`, `ca-kind`, plus `ca-actions` (leaf) or `ca-next-scope` (drill) |[[Protocol|$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/protocol]] §"Worked example 1–4" (or create it in-palette: ''Manage entries'' → ''+ New entry…'') |
|A new action for an entity type |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` |`ca-name`, `ca-kind`, `ca-entity-type` and/or `ca-applies` |[[Protocol]] §"Worked example 3–5" (or create it in-palette: ''Manage actions'' → ''+ New action…'') |
|A new search-filter pill |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/filter` |`ca-filter-name`, `ca-filter-expr` |[[Protocol]] §"Worked example — Title-prefix filter" |
|A new visibility (hide-predicate) pill |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility` |`ca-visibility-name`, `ca-visibility-expr` |[[Protocol]] §"Worked example — Hide a group" |
|A new view (root-stage strategy) |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/view` |`ca-view-name`, `ca-view-roots` |[[Protocol]] §"Views" |
|A new channel (sub-component of a view) |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/channel` |`ca-channel-name`, `ca-channel-roots` |[[Protocol]] §"Multi-channel views" |
|A new grouping axis |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/axis` |`ca-axis-name`, `ca-axis-key` |[[Protocol]] §"Axes" (or create it in-palette: ''Manage axes'' → ''+ New axis…'') |
|A new leader-key gesture |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader` |`ca-leader-key`, `ca-leader-actions` |[[Protocol]] §"Leader keys" |
|A new side-preview template |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview` |`ca-preview-applies` or `ca-preview-context`, body wikitext |[[Protocol]] §"Side preview" |
|A new row icon |`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/row-icon` |`ca-row-icon-applies`, `ca-row-icon-glyph`, action/message |[[Protocol]] §"Row icons" |

If you find yourself wishing for a tag or field that doesn't exist, you're probably looking for a new ''kind of cascade primitive'' — please open an issue rather than patching the widget. The widget aims to be a constant; the protocol is the extension surface.

! Local dev cycle

You're editing tiddlers in `dev-wiki/`. The filesystem-watcher plugin (also rimir) picks up changes in `dev-wiki/tiddlers/` and `dev-wiki/plugins/`. Everything declarative is hot — close & reopen the palette to pick up new entries / actions / leaders / axes / filters / visibility / views / channels / side-previews / row-icons.

JS modules (`widgets/cp-*.js`, custom filter operators, startup modules) are NOT hot — restart the wiki server:

```
# from project root, manually
node node_modules/tiddlywiki/tiddlywiki.js dev-wiki --listen
```

Or use `bin/tw start`.

! Discovering what's loaded — the Diagnostics drill

Open the palette → ''Configurations'' → ''Diagnostics''. Three drills:

* ''Loaded actions'' — every action tiddler the engine sees. Use this to verify your action is tagged correctly and its `ca-entity-type` / `ca-applies` resolves.
* ''Loaded entries'' — every entry tiddler. Use this to spot a stray `ca-position-<view>` that demotes your entry to the wrong place.
* ''Loaded settings'' — every `setting`-tagged tiddler. Use this when a new setting row isn't appearing in the Settings menu.

The diagnostic drills are filter-driven — adding more diagnostic listings is just one more entry tiddler with a `ca-next-scope` filter.

! Debugging action discovery

When an action doesn't appear where you expect:

# Open the palette, navigate to the target row.
# Hit Space — if you see ''empty list, no actions'', the engine found zero applicable actions for this row.
# Three discovery paths are unioned and deduplicated:
## ''Catalogue'' — does the action's `ca-entity-type` match the row's bound `entityType`? (Bound by `ca-channel-row-entity-type` on the emitting channel.)
## ''Configured-field bridge'' — is `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/entity-type-field` set to a field, AND does the row's tiddler have that field's value matching the action's `ca-entity-type`? (E.g. `rimir/kind` sets it to `kind.type`.)
## ''Filter'' — when the action declares `ca-applies`, does the filter return non-empty for `<currentTiddler>` = row title?
# Every discovered action is then narrowed by its `ca-action-when` (if set) — same `<currentTiddler>` binding.
# Open the browser console — `ca-applies` / `ca-action-when` evaluation errors are logged (no silent failures).

! Backwards-compat conventions

When evolving the protocol, never break authored tiddlers. The plugin's track record:

* ''Aliases.'' `ca-view-source` is honoured as a back-compat alias for `ca-view-roots`. Pattern: read the new field first; fall back to the old one. Document the alias in `doc/protocol.tid` and `doc/reference.tid`.
* ''Phased rollout.'' When a complex refactor is needed (e.g. the 0.0.37 → 0.0.38 multi-channel view model), ship the new primitives first with back-compat, then rewrite the engine on top in the next version. Two-phase landings keep risk down.
* ''Soft deprecation'' — when an old form should no longer be used, emit a one-time `console.warn` via `cp.deprecationWarning(key, message)` (cp-utils.js). Never per-keystroke; never silent removal. Surface active deprecations in the ''Diagnostics → Deprecations'' sub-entry so users find them without reading the changelog.

! Versioning

''Default bump is patch'' (`+0.0.1`). Bump minor/major only when the user explicitly asks. After any visible change, also add a row to `changelog.tid` (`|!Version |!Date |!Changes |` table).

! Testing your additions

Cascade-palette is the prime ''extending another plugin'' reference plugin — so testing your authoring channel matters. Two patterns work without touching JS:

''CLI gotchas fixture'' (`tw-tests/gotchas/fixtures/<your-slug>/`) — small standalone wiki with `tiddlywiki.info` loading cascade-palette + your contribution, `tiddlers/RunTest.tid` rendering a representative filter (e.g. action discovery for a specific entity type, or position resolution for an entry), and `expected.txt` capturing the byte-stable output. Run with `bin/tw test:gotchas <your-slug>`. Bootstrap `expected.txt` via `UPDATE=1 ./tw-tests/gotchas/run.sh <your-slug>`.

''Wiki test spec'' — for authoring-channel behaviour like cascade-position-fallback or filter substitution semantics, write a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/wiki-test-spec` in `tw-tests/test-edition/tiddlers/` with `Setup`, `Description`, `ExpectedResult`, and `Narrative` sections. See [[tw-gotchas-testing#Wiki-based test ExpectedResult…]] for the trailing-newline trap.

''Jasmine spec'' (`tw-tests/test-edition/tests/cascade-palette/*.spec.js`) — for pure-function unit tests of any JS utility you contribute (e.g. a new sort comparator, a sanitisation helper). Run with `bin/tw test cascade-palette`.

! What lives where (engine source layout)

```
dev-wiki/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/
├── plugin.info
├── widgets/
│   ├── cascade-palette-widget.js   # orchestrator: state + render + render + lifecycle
│   ├── cascade-palette-startup.js  # mounts widget in document.body at boot
│   ├── cp-constants.js             # tag names, message strings, defaults
│   ├── cp-filter-ops.js            # custom filter operator(s)
│   └── cp-*.js                     # subsystem libraries (each patches the prototype)
├── actions/, entries/, axes/, views/, channels/, filters/, visibility/, leaders/, reach/, row-icons/, settings/
│                                   # shipped declarative content
├── config/                         # raw $:/config/... tiddlers (engine-facing)
├── diagnostics/                    # entries that drill into loaded-* lists
├── doc/                            # doc-template doc tiddlers (you are here)
├── field/                          # search-in-field pill tiddlers (not ca-bind-field!)
├── help/                           # in-app help tiddlers
├── templates/                      # detail templates
├── styles.tid, icon.tid, readme.tid, changelog.tid, settings.tid, …
```

For engine internals (how the widget actually works), see [[TW Internals|$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/tw-internals]].

